obo:UBERON_0002421  a  owl:Class .

obo:ECO_0000279  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_983  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: DLC antibody co-localizes with PSD-95 and F-actin at excitatory synapses in cultured hippocampal neurons (Fig. 5). Quantitative immunogold EM localization of DLC in the PSD and dendritic spine (Fig. 6A-H). Enrichment of DLC in PSD fractions (Fig. 6I). Colocalization of DLC with GKAP and PSD-95 by immunoEM (Fig. 7).\n\nThe antibodies used in this study can not distinguish between DLC1 and DLC2 (98% similarity between these proteins)\n\n3/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the localization to the postsynapse of Venus-tagged Dlc2 the EM data with the antibody that does not distinguish between DLC1 and DLC2 I think this data on PSD localization can be transferred to the DLC2 protein.. Experimental description: From M&M:\nHippocampal neuronal cultures prepared from 18 day embryonic rats\nPull-down experiments were done with whole rat brain homogenate\nImmunoprecipitations were done from rat forebrain synaptosomes (P2 fraction)\nFor EM immunocytochemistry, male Sprague Dawley rats (225-375 gm; Charles River, Raleigh, NC) were anesthetized" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_983" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

